3/6) In the midst of the current Discord "WL-grind" meta, we decided to take an anti-grind approach and shorten the selection time for our allowlist by hand-vetting as much as possible, and also bringing other long-term communities into our process via Friendships/Partnerships.🤝

2/6) From the start, our growth was organic. We didn't want to artificially hype or engagement-farm our project leading up to launch and had to turn down countless marketing proposals. We believe that authenticity is key to ensuring the longevity of any NFT brand. 🗺️
1/6) A post-launch recap, and how we strived to help set a launch standard for the next iteration of NFT projects/communities in Web3 (summary)👇 🧵
